 the spiritual qualities of the revolutionary mind. From Ah Q to Lei Feng investigates the continual clash of these contrasting models of the mind provided by Freud and revolutionary Chinese culture, and explores how writers and filmmakers negotiated with the implications of each model. .  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aChinese literaturexHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aChinese literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and historyxChina. 0aLiterature and historyzChina. 0aPsychoanalysis and literaturexChina. 0aPsychoanalysis and literaturezChina. 0aPsychoanalysis and motion picturesxChina. 0aPsychoanalysis and motion pictureszChina. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804769822zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804769822423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804769822.jpg  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles